Anti-apartheid activist Winnie Madikizela Mandela been discharged from hospital, the Mandela family said on Tuesday afternoon. “I’m pleased to be going back home where I’ll be able to rest and fully recuperate from the short illness. The doctors and nurses who looked after me were wonderful,” said Madikizela Mandela. Madikizela Mandela, 81, was admitted at Milpark Hospital in Johannesburg 10 days ago with a kidney infection and also suffering from exhaustion. The family says it is delighted that she has now been discharged from hospital. - SAnews.gov.za